Solutions Architect


Mitsubishi HC Capital Canada 

Burlington, ON, Canada 




Job Description



By joining Mitsubishi HC Capital Canada, you will be part of an exceptional team offering flexible and adaptative commercial Equipment Financing solutions to Canadian businesses. Whether it’s leasing, factoring, inventory finance or asset-based lending, our teams are dedicated to offer the best service to our customers.

In 2021, our company was awarded by Waterstone’s “Canada’s Most Admired Culture”. Our collaborative culture, empowerment, employee’s development, open-mindedness and respectful work-environment were success factors!

With a specialized team for sustainable development and a committee focusing on giving back to the community, we strive to make a difference in societal improvement.



About The Solutions Architect Role



As a part of the Information Technology team, you will help transform our current monolithic architecture into a domain-driven microservice-oriented architecture to ease system to system integration and data governance. You will translate complex business problems into technical solutions and complex technical solutions into business capabilities and functionalities. You will be working on projects supporting the digital transformation of the organization, ensuring quality and on-time delivery of assigned deliverables.



Your Main Responsibilities Will Be




Be responsible for architectural design, issues and resolution considerations among all projects;

Apply industry best practices to create scalable and secure solutions that have superior technical performance while offering the best security patterns;

Work with product owners/project managers to intimately understand product vision;

Identify options and make recommendations on the technology solutions we can implement to meet the business goals;

Work with a cross-functional technology team to design and implement those technology recommendations;

Demonstrate strategic business acumen and understanding of organization strategy, as well as the ability to design information systems to deliver that strategy;

Mentor and advise other team members.




The Profile We Are Looking For




Bachelor’s degree in a technical area of study (computer science, mathematics, engineering, etc.) or other BS degree with a concentration in computer science or information systems;

Total IT experience of at least 10 years with 3-5 years in solution architecture;

2 years of relevant experience in the leasing/financial industry;

Deep understanding of business strategy and the ability to craft software architecture plans to support business outcomes;

Proven experience architecting and supporting implementation of infrastructure components for software implementation, both on-premises and in-cloud;

Knowledge/experience with architecting full-stack technology solutions, including backend, microservices, data layers, API gateways, etc.;

.NET (Core) experience as a key leader/advisor on the architecture, design and development of wide-reaching technology components;

Excellent organizational and analytical skills;

Excellent collaborator and positive leadership;

Highly proficient with Microsoft Office 365 applications;

Excellent oral and written communication skills (any knowledge of French would be a precious asset as we offer services in both official languages);

Any knowledge of Agile methodology would be an asset.




What We Have To Offer



Full time position


37.5 hour work-week, Monday to Friday


Hybrid work environment (working from home and the office) with options to work from offices in:


Burlington, Ontario

Calgary, Alberta

Montréal, Québec

Laval, Québec

Trois-Rivières, Québec

Québec, Québec


Compensation plan including bonus based on your individual performance as well as the Company’s results

Competitive benefits package including:


Vacation, sick and personal days given on day one

Collective insurance including long-term disability, life insurance, medical, dental and vision care as well as virtual healthcare

RRSP

Range of wellness initiatives including Employee and Family Assistance Program and virtual health and development platforms


Professional growth opportunities through our internal postings and online learning platform



